      "date": "2012-05-16 04:43:58.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: (1 inline comment)\n\nNed,\nis LLNL still using clients with kernels < 2.6.18?  We are actively removing support for kernels older than RHEL5 2.6.18 for the 2.3 release, so this would be news to us that you are using such clients in production.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "4a252409cb905a78e0fb8d47aad95454e369bd5f",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 126,
        "name": "Ned Bass",
        "email": "bass6@llnl.gov",
        "username": "nedbass"
      },
      "date": "2012-05-16 16:49:14.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> is LLNL still using clients with kernels < 2.6.18?\n\nYes, our BG/P system runs 2.6.16 on the IO nodes.  We decided to start testing the 2.1 client on BG/P mainly due to LU-1378 and our desire to discontinue local maintenance of our 1.8 branch.  I realize that continued support for these kernels is not something we can expect in future Lustre releases.  But we'll probably be running and supporting 2.1 at least until we retire our BG/P systems, so landing fixes in this branch is much less burdensome for us.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
