          "date": "2012-05-16 18:34:38.000000000",
          "tz": -420
        },
        "subject": "LU-1411 obdclass: compatibility for kernels < 2.6.18",
        "message": "LU-1411 obdclass: compatibility for kernels < 2.6.18\n\nlustre_get_sb() conditionally calls get_sb_nodev() with a struct\nlustre_mount_data2 * for kernels 2.6.18 and newer, and a void * data\npointer for older kernels.  However, lustre_fill_super()\nunconditionally casts its void *data argument to a struct\nlustre_mount_data2 *, which causes a crash when we deference into it\non older kernels.  To fix this, add conditional code to\nlustre_fill_super() to support older kernels.\n\nSigned-off-by: Ned Bass <bass6@llnl.gov>\nChange-Id: I11ee910822db3933da3c57e4ef1484a7de95dff2\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/b2_1"
    }
